# <type>(<optional scope>): <subject — imperative, lowercase, <=72 chars>
#
# Why this change is needed (1–3 sentences). Focus on the WHY,
# not the WHAT — the diff already shows what changed.
#
# - Bullet points for notable details, if helpful.
# - Reference REQ-IDs / plan-IDs sparingly — PR description carries detail.
#
# Co-Authored-By: ...
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Conventional Commit types (Semantic Release driver):
#   feat:     New feature                         → Minor bump
#   fix:      Bug fix                             → Patch bump
#   docs:     Documentation only                  → Patch bump
#   chore:    Maintenance / tooling               → Patch bump
#   refactor: Code change without behavior change → Patch bump
#   test:     Tests only                          → Patch bump
#   style:    Formatting / CSS                    → Patch bump
#   perf:     Performance                         → Patch bump
#   ci:       CI/CD only                          → No release
#
# Breaking changes: add "BREAKING CHANGE: ..." in the footer → Major bump.
#
# Format:  <type>(<optional scope>): <description>
# Example: feat(scoring): add penalty point deduction
#
# Subject rules:
#   - imperative mood ("add", not "added"/"adds")
#   - no trailing period
#   - <= 72 chars
#
# Squash-merge subjects MUST follow the same format — Semantic Release
# does not fire on PR titles alone.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
